product_name: MACMini Hyper Real Fresh Canvas Cream-To-Foam Face Cleanser
summary: SummaryMAC Hyper Real Fresh Canvas Cream-To-Foam Cleanser, is a luxurious, transformative gentle cleanser that deeply yet gently cleanses, purifies, maintains skin's moisture, and smooths skin immediately. This formula does not drag or dry out the skin, revealing a healthy-looking, clean glow.
details: DetailsBenefitsDeeply yet gently cleanses and purifies skin without dryingRemoves makeup, including long-wearing face and lip products, dirt, excess oil and pollutantsLeaves complexion comfortably smooth and cleanFeatures a sensorial texture that transforms from a soft cream into a luxurious latherSkin feels fresh with a healthy-looking, clean glowFor all skin typesKey IngredientsResilient+Rare Japenese Peony Extract, Cationic Hyaluronic Acid & 20% Glycerin: Helps to maintin skin's moisture for fresh, supple, petal-smooth skin that’s always skincare-ready.FeaturesDeeply cleanse your complexion with MAC's gentle, decadent cream-to-foam cleanserRemoves makeup and dissolves dirt, excess oil and pollutants while smoothing skin immediately and over timeItem 2618049How To Use•Apply cleanser twice a day, morning and evening, as part of your Hyper Real skincare routine.•Take a pearl-sized amount to fingertips and add lukewarm water to lather into a rich foam.•Massage onto damp skin using circular motions, avoiding the eye area.•Use Artist-crafted Lush Lather Technique by massaging the formula from the center of the face outward to create a luxurious lather.•Rinse with warm water thoroughly and pat dry.•Pair with Hyper Real Fresh Canvas Cleansing Oil for clean skin with a healthy-looking glow.IngredientsWater\Aqua\Eau, Glycerin, Myristic Acid, Behenic Acid, Sodium Methyl Cocoyl Taurate, Palmitic Acid, Potassium Hydroxide, Lauric Acid, Stearic Acid, Algae Extract, Paeoniaalbiflora, Flower Extract, Hydroxypropyltrimonium Hyaluronate, Caffeine, Butylene Glycol, Sorbitol, Sodium Hyaluronate, Sucrose, Xanthan Gum, Polyquaternium-7, Tetrasodium Edta, Disodium Edta, Fragrance (Parfum), Benzyl Salicylate, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Chlorphenesin, Potassium Sorbate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Sodium Benzoate ≪Iln52340≫Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: •Apply cleanser twice a day, morning and evening, as part of your Hyper Real skincare routine.•Take a pearl-sized amount to fingertips and add lukewarm water to lather into a rich foam.•Massage onto damp skin using circular motions, avoiding the eye area.•Use Artist-crafted Lush Lather Technique by massaging the formula from the center of the face outward to create a luxurious lather.•Rinse with warm water thoroughly and pat dry.•Pair with Hyper Real Fresh Canvas Cleansing Oil for clean skin with a healthy-looking glow.

reviews.headline: Yes!!
reviews.comments: I received a small sample that lasted me 14 face washes. It foams up so well when you add water that you don't need very much. I love a foamy cleanser, and the fact that this facewash literally makes my skin squeek. It also leaves a shine and removes all my makeup.. I have no idea why you wouldn't want a face wash that truly cleanses. I purchased this and its a huge bottle, so for the price it will definitely last!

reviews.headline: Not horrible not the best
reviews.comments: If you have dry skin I would steer clear I find it to be a very drying cleanser and leaves you're skin with an also squeaky clean feeling which personally I don't love but that might be perfect for someone.

reviews.headline: Only face wash I've used since November
reviews.comments:
- Favorite face wash!
- non-stripping
- the only face wash that doesnt make my skin feel tight
- literally dont need much! Foam up just the smallest amount in your hands, then wash your face

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: This cleans my face so well, and a little bit does go a long way.. its foamy and feels soft and luxurious. I need the big bottle!

reviews.headline: Would buy again
reviews.comments: Great cleanser. My face feels really clean after using, but it's not harsh on my skin.  It smells lovely too. I highly recommend MAC's skincare line. I will definitely buy again.

reviews.headline: I won't go without this stuff!
reviews.comments: I've been an avid mac user for as long as I've been wearing makeup, it had no idea they had a cleanser. When I saw it I immediately purchased. This stuff is absolutely amazing. Its creamy on your skin, deep cleanses, gets all the makeup  off, doesn't leave me dry, and smells AMAZING!!

reviews.headline: It is nice, but not for the price point
reviews.comments: I do like it. it is lightly scented so buyer beware. it's a lush foam. a little goes a long way. However for what it does (which is just clean)...its a bit overpriced.  and I will not repurchase for that reason. it doesn't do anything extraordinary.

reviews.headline: Powerful Cleanser
reviews.comments: This cleanser really deep cleansing and takes away all oil, dirt, makeup, pollutants off your skin. This cleanser is no joke. It's excellent for oily greasy skin, but I would be a little nervous to recommend to someone with dry skin. I love this cleanser

reviews.headline: Worst cleanser.
reviews.comments: Normally i love MAC products, but this cleanser is HORRIBLE. The worst I've ever used. It does not remove makeup but somehow still leaves my skin feeling SUPER stripped. If you use even just a LITTLE too much the chemical vapors from the cleanser burn my eyes. My skin and eyes are not sensitive and I have no allergies to products.

reviews.headline: Love it!  With one tiny change …
reviews.comments: One of the best cleansers ever, especially as the second step in a double cleanse when you use the Cleansing Oil as the first. My skin feels fresh, hydrated, bouncy. My one tiny issue - I wish it was a flip top instead of a screw top cap. Trying to uncap it with wet hands is a bit of a mess. Still, that's a minor issue and more of a preference. I have purchased this more and once and will keep it up!

reviews.headline: Designer Ivory Soap
reviews.comments: This smells like Ivory Soap and straps my face just like it. This left me with that unpleasant squeaky clean face. I'm super dry and dehydrated so I have no oils to spare. Save your face and skip this

reviews.headline: I would by this product again
reviews.comments: I love that ULTA carries MAC products!

reviews.headline: No I won't buy again.
reviews.comments: Do not like the MAC facial cleanser.  Leaves a sticky feeling on my face.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The Hyper Real Fresh Canvas Cleanser has undeniably set a new standard in my skincare routine, and the cream-to-foam formulation is nothing short of a revelation. From its transformative texture to its revitalizing effects, this cleanser has become a daily indulgence that I eagerly anticipate.

The standout feature of this cleanser is its unique cream-to-foam formula. As soon as it touches the skin, the luxurious cream effortlessly glides on, providing a soothing and calming sensation. What sets it apart is the seamless transition into a lightweight foam upon contact with water. This dual-action ensures a thorough cleanse that removes impurities, excess oil, and makeup while maintaining a gentle touch.

One of the most impressive aspects of Hyper Real's cleanser is its ability to cleanse without stripping the skin of its natural moisture. It strikes the perfect balance, leaving my face feeling refreshed and clean, yet incredibly soft and supple. The hydrating properties are a game-changer for someone like me with combination skin – a thorough cleanse without the dreaded tightness.

The packaging of the cleanser is both practical and visually appealing. The sleek design adds a touch of sophistication to my skincare shelf. It's evident that attention to detail has been considered in every aspect of this product.

The scent is subtle yet invigorating, creating a spa-like experience during each use. It's a delightful blend that adds a sensory element to my skincare routine without being overpowering or irritating.

I have noticed a positive difference in my skin's clarity and texture since incorporating this cleanser into my daily routine. It seems to promote a healthy glow and has become a vital step in achieving a fresh canvas before applying any additional skincare products.
faceoff_positive.headline: Essential item in your skin care routine

faceoff_negative.comments: I was excited to try this cleaner as the packaging is minimalistic yet looks fancy. The smell reminds me of the Soap & Glory brand, very rich and mature as well as that vintage feel. Unfortunately, I noticed that this cleanser doesn't hold up in comparison to my favorites and it's twice the price. It also doesn't much much sense to me that you can't use it anywhere near the eyes, as it's described as a foaming cleanser and foaming cleansers expand. However, this cleanser doesn't foam up as advertised and it's very drying. I mistakenly had the misfortune of putting this near my eyes and it stung worse than any cleanser I've ever used. It also doesn't cleanse very deeply as I noticed there was some makeup still on my face and had to use another cleanser to get the job done. I truly wouldn't recommend this to anyone especially those with dry skin like mine. There are so many more amazing cleansers on the market that are more affordable and won't make your eyes burn.
faceoff_negative.headline: Worst Cleanser I've Ever Used
